{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Floop\u8217's REAPER Scripts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This repository contains a collection of {\b JSFX effects} and {\b Lua scripts} for {\b REAPER}, focused on audio processing, monitoring, and workflow enhancement.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All tools are released as {\b free and open-source software}.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Repository Structure\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The tools are organized into the following directories:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 scripts/}: Lua scripts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 effects/}: JSFX effects\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Each tool is contained in its own folder and typically includes:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab the script or effect file ({\f1 .lua} or {\f1 .jsfx})\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab a dedicated {\f1 README.md} with usage instructions and details\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This structure allows the repository to be used both:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab via {\b ReaPack}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab and by manually downloading individual tools from GitHub\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Automatic Installation (Recommended \u8211- ReaPack)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open {\b REAPER}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Go to {\b Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Import Repositories\u8230 ?}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Paste the following URL:\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 https://github.com/floop-s/floops-reaper-scripts/raw/main/index.xml}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab The repository will appear in ReaPack. Browse and install scripts or effects as needed.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Manual Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Download the repository\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Clone it with Git or download it as a ZIP file.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Locate the REAPER resource path\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab In REAPER, go to {\b Options \u8594 ? Show REAPER resource path in explorer / finder}\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Install the files\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Lua scripts}: Copy {\f1 .lua} files into the {\f1 Scripts} folder.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b JSFX effects}: Copy {\f1 .jsfx} files into the {\f1 Effects} folder.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Refresh REAPER\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Lua scripts}: Open the {\b Actions List} ({\f1 ?}) \u8594 ? {\b New Action \u8594 ? Load ReaScript\u8230 ?}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b JSFX effects}: Open the FX Browser and press {\b F5} to rescan effects.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Refer to each tool\u8217's own {\f1 README.md} for specific usage instructions and requirements.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Compatibility\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Primary platform:} Developed and tested on {\b Windows}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b macOS / Linux:} Some scripts are designed to be cross-platform, but not all tools are tested on these systems. Compatibility and stability are not guaranteed. Feedback is welcome.\sa180\par}
